body: [array includes] ArrayIncludesIndexofAssembler and specific TF_BUILTIN entries in builtins/builtins-array-gen.cc: handles PACKED_SMI, HOLEY_SMI, PACKED_ELEMENTS, HOLEY_ELEMENTS, PACKED_DOUBLE, HOLEY_DOUBLE. Precondition checks: BranchIfFastJSArrayForRead(receiver,...), LoadElementsKind dispatch, LoadFastJSArrayLength, fromIndex init handles Smis and undefined, Smi checks for length and empty. SameValueZero: NaN handling in Packed and Holey doubles (nan_loop) and hole treated as undefined in holey doubles (hole_loop). For Smi/Object: ident_loop and heap_num_loop handle NaN differently; includes treats hole as undefined via undef_loop. See code lines in builtins/builtins-array-gen.cc
explanation: This entry captures the generated builtins implementation for Array.prototype.includes and the internal splitting by elements kind in ArrayIncludesIndexofAssembler. It documents key branches for fast-path checks, elements kind dispatch, same-value-zero behavior (NaN, hole as undefined), and fromIndex/length handling.
